category: Libs
requires: cygwin libgcc1 libgraphite2_2.0.0 libiconv2 libicu48 libstdc++6
sdesc: "Font rendering capabilities for complex non-Roman writing systems (utilities)"
ldesc: "Graphite2 is a project within SIL's Non-Roman Script Initiative and
Language Software Development groups to provide rendering capabilities for
complex non-Roman writing systems. Graphite can be used to create
'smart fonts' capable of displaying writing systems with various complex
behaviors. With respect to the Text Encoding Model, Graphite handles the
'Rendering' aspect of writing system implementation."
